doc.after: The Royal Malaysian Air Force (Tentera Udara Diraja Malaysia) has eight F/A-18Ds.[62] Delivery of the aircraft started in March 1997 until August 1997.[49] The air force split their order between the F/A-18 and the Mikoyan MiG-29.[63] Three Hornets were employed together with five UK-made BAE Hawk 208 in an airstrike on the Royal Security Forces of the Sultanate of Sulu and North Borneo terrorist hideout on 5 March 2013, occupying part of Borneo, just before the joint forces of Malaysian Army and Royal Malaysia Police operatives launched an assault in the 2013 Lahad Datu standoff.[64] This was the first shot fired in combat by the Malaysian Hornets.[citation needed]
